      <article><b>14</b><span>Tri-hybrid driver architecture</span></article>
      <article><b>4 EST</b><span>Electrostatic super tweeters</span></article>
      <article><b>5-way</b><span>Passive crossover network</span></article>
      <article><b>7 Ohm</b><span>Super-Low Flat Impedance</span></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cp-section cp-story">
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-story__grid">
      <div>
        <p class="cp-kicker">Design Story</p>
        <h2>Blue fire, black shell, fast air.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="cp-prose">
        <p>Canary Pro refines the original Canary formula into a denser, more controlled architecture. The faceplate keeps the electric, fractured-color identity that defined Canary. The acoustic design underneath is tighter and more deliberate.</p>
        <p>A dual-diaphragm isobaric woofer system moves more air without asking the shell to grow. Four electrostatic super tweeters carry the top octave and spatial cues. Eight balanced armatures fill the range in between, with a five-way crossover keeping each driver group in its lane.</p>
        <p>The result is a flagship that stays fast, vivid, and layered — without thinning out the weight that keeps instruments believable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cp-section cp-section--dark cp-explosion" aria-labelledby="cp-explosion-title">
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-explosion__frame">
      <figure class="cp-explosion__media">
        {% render 'aaw-responsive-asset-image', file: 'canary-pro-exploded-serial.png', alt: 'Exploded Canary Pro construction render showing driver modules, printed chamber, shell, faceplate, socket, and nozzle', width: '2000', height: '1453', loading: 'lazy' %}
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-explosion__copy">
      <p class="cp-kicker">Exploded View</p>
      <h2 id="cp-explosion-title">Fourteen drivers in a wearable shell</h2>
      <p>The exploded view walks through the signal path: 2-pin socket, acoustic chamber, balanced armature arrays, electrostatic modules, isobaric woofer system, precision shell, stainless nozzle, and the Canary Pro faceplate — all stacked into a monitor that sits comfortably in the ear.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="cp-architecture" class="cp-section cp-section--dark cp-architecture">
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-section-head">
      <p class="cp-kicker">Transducer Architecture</p>
      <h2>Fourteen drivers, five bands, one flat load.</h2>
      <p>Canary Pro earns its driver count through the division of work. The five-way passive crossover splits the signal by frequency band. SLFI reshapes the electrical load so the monitor stays near 7 Ohm across the audible range — no wild swings when you switch from a dongle to a desktop amp.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-architecture__grid">
      <article class="cp-driver-visual" aria-label="Canary Pro generated driver configuration">
        <figure class="cp-driver-visual__media">
          {% render 'aaw-responsive-asset-image', file: 'canary-pro-driver-render-clean.jpg', alt: 'Canary Pro 3D rendered driver configuration without baked-in text labels', width: '3840', height: '2160', loading: 'lazy' %}
        </figure>
        <div class="cp-driver-visual__overlay" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--left cp-driver-label--est">Electrostatic Super<br>Tweeter X 4</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--left cp-driver-label--mid">Mid Range Balanced<br>Armature X 4</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--left cp-driver-label--midhigh">Mid-High Balanced<br>Armature X 4</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--left cp-driver-label--woofer">Isobaric Dual<br>Dynamic Driver</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--right cp-driver-label--shell">Precision 3D Printed Shell<br>with Stainless Nozzle</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--right cp-driver-label--crossover">5 Way Passive<br>Crossover</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--right cp-driver-label--socket">Endurance 2PIN<br>Socket</span>
          <span class="cp-driver-label cp-driver-label--right cp-driver-label--faceplate">Canary Pro<br>Exclusive Design</span>
        </div>
      </article>
      <div class="cp-driver-map" aria-label="Canary Pro driver layout">
        <article><span>01</span><b>2 woofers</b><p>Dual isobaric dynamic diaphragms create low-end pressure with cleaner excursion control.</p></article>
        <article><span>02</span><b>2 low-range</b><p>Dedicated balanced armatures bridge bass weight into the lower mids without clouding the center image.</p></article>
        <article><span>03</span><b>2 mid-range</b><p>Vocal body, instrumental tone, and the information that makes a mix feel human.</p></article>
        <article><span>04</span><b>4 mid-high</b><p>Presence, snap, and upper harmonics, separated before the EST array takes over.</p></article>
        <article><span>05</span><b>4 EST</b><p>Electrostatic super tweeters supply extension, air, and the fine spatial layer above conventional armatures.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cp-section cp-section--dark cp-slfi" aria-labelledby="cp-slfi-title">
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-slfi__grid">
      <figure class="cp-slfi__graph">
        {% render 'aaw-responsive-asset-image', file: 'canary-pro-slfi.png', alt: 'Canary Pro SLFI impedance and frequency response graph', width: '2000', height: '1261', loading: 'lazy' %}
        <figcaption>Measured against the response curve, SLFI keeps Canary Pro close to a flat 7 Ohm load across the audible range.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="cp-slfi__copy">
        <p class="cp-kicker">Super-Low Flat Impedance</p>
        <h2 id="cp-slfi-title">The tuning stays put.</h2>
        <p>Most multi-driver IEMs shift tonal balance when the source impedance changes. SLFI reshapes the balanced armature load from inductive toward resistive, holding impedance near 7 Ohm across the frequency range. The result is one tuning that stays put — whether you're on a dongle, a DAP, or a full desktop chain.</p>
        <div class="cp-slfi__benefits" aria-label="Listener benefits of SLFI">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Source-to-source consistency</h3>
            <p>The bass, midrange, and treble balance holds shape when you switch between players, adapters, and amplifiers.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Clean crossover handoff</h3>
            <p>A stable electrical load lets the five-way crossover divide work between drivers without the bands pulling each other out of shape.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Repeatable listening</h3>
            <p>What you hear at a desk, on a portable rig, or at a show stays close to the intended Canary Pro tuning.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cp-slfi__facts" aria-label="SLFI technical facts">
        <article><span>Target load</span><b>7 ohm</b><p>Flat across frequency, not just a single nominal number.</p></article>
        <article><span>Driver behavior</span><b>Resistive</b><p>Balanced armatures are managed away from source-sensitive inductive swings.</p></article>
        <article><span>Listener result</span><b>Consistent</b><p>More reliable tone across portable and desktop source chains.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

