  <section class="cp-section cp-build">
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-build__grid">
      <div class="cp-build__copy">
        <p class="cp-kicker">3D Printed Acoustic System</p>
        <h2>Printed chamber, metal nozzle, tuned path lengths.</h2>
        <p>The enclosure and woofer acoustic chamber are printed separately, then assembled into a nozzle system that controls path length and pressure. The digital workflow keeps the driver matrix consistent from pair to pair.</p>
        <p>Simulation determines phasing and placement. Printing turns that geometry into a repeatable acoustic structure. Hand finishing gives the shell its final surface and fit.</p>
