  <section class="cp-section cp-faq">
    <div class="cp-wrap cp-faq__grid">
      <div>
        <p class="cp-kicker">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Before you choose Canary Pro</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="cp-faq__list">
        <details open>
          <summary><span>What makes Canary Pro different from the original Canary?</span></summary>
          <p>Canary Pro keeps the hybrid Canary identity but rebuilds it around a 14-driver matrix: quad electrostatic super tweeters, dual isobaric dynamic woofers, eight balanced armatures, a 5-way passive crossover, and Super-Low Flat Impedance for consistent source pairing.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What is the driver configuration?</span></summary>
          <p>2 isobaric dynamic woofers, 2 low-range BA, 2 mid-range BA, 4 mid-high BA, and 4 electrostatic super tweeters. The five driver groups are managed by a 5-way passive crossover.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What does SLFI do and why does it matter?</span></summary>
          <p>Super-Low Flat Impedance reshapes the balanced armature electrical load from inductive toward resistive, holding the monitor near 7 Ohm across the frequency range. This reduces tonal shifts when switching between sources with different output impedances — dongle, DAP, or desktop.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What is the isobaric woofer system?</span></summary>
          <p>Two dynamic drivers are arranged in an isobaric (constant-pressure) configuration. This doubles the effective diaphragm area for better low-end control without increasing the shell size.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Is Canary Pro suitable for stage monitoring?</span></summary>
          <p>Yes. Canary Pro is designed for critical listening and professional use. The custom-fit option provides additional isolation and stability for stage work. Final suitability depends on personal fit, isolation needs, and monitoring level.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What source is recommended for Canary Pro?</span></summary>
          <p>With 106dB sensitivity and a flat 7 Ohm impedance, Canary Pro pairs well with most portable players, dongles, DAPs, and desktop amplifiers. A clean, low-output-impedance source is recommended for lowest noise floor.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What is the difference between universal and custom fit?</span></summary>
          <p>The universal model ships with SpinFit silicone tips, AAW foam tips, and assorted silicone tips for an immediate fit. Custom-fit monitors are shaped from ear impressions for a personalized seal. Both share the same 14-driver acoustic design.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What comes in the box?</span></summary>
          <p>Canary Pro includes a 48-inch Null Audio Lune cable with 4.4mm balanced termination, leather carry case, cleaning tool, owner's club card, SpinFit silicone tips, AAW foam tips, assorted silicone tips, and a 1-year limited warranty.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Does Canary Pro come with a warranty?</span></summary>
          <p>Yes. Canary Pro includes a 1-year limited warranty covering manufacturing defects under normal use. For support, contact AAW Singapore or the authorized dealer where you purchased it.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Where can I demo Canary Pro?</span></summary>
          <p>In Singapore, you can audition Canary Pro at the AAW Office, Zeppelin & Co., JABEN, or AV One. Outside Singapore, AAW works with specialist audio stores across Hong Kong, Japan, China, South Korea, and Thailand. Use the store locator to find the closest listening point.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

